snippet.title: Wicked: For Good | Final Trailer
snippet.description:
The final #WickedForGood trailer is here ✨ Watch now.

Pre-order Wicked: For Good - The Soundtrack 💚🩷 available November 21st at https://wickedthesoundtrack.lnk.to/forgood
-----
TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@wickedmovie
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/wickedmovie
X: https://twitter.com/wickedmovie
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/wickedmovie
Official Site: https://wickedmovie.com

And now whatever way our stories end, I know you have rewritten mine by being my friend …

Last year’s global cinematic cultural sensation, which became the most successful Broadway film adaptation of all time, now reaches its epic, electrifying, emotional conclusion in Wicked: For Good. 

Directed once again by award-winning director Jon M. Chu and starring the spectacular returning cast, led by Academy Award® nominated superstars Cynthia Erivo and Ariana Grande, the final chapter of the untold story of the witches of Oz begins with Elphaba and Glinda estranged and living with the consequences of their choices. 

Elphaba (Cynthia Erivo), now demonized as The Wicked Witch of the West, lives in exile, hidden within the Ozian forest while continuing her fight for the freedom of Oz’s silenced Animals and desperately trying to expose the truth she knows about The Wizard (Jeff Goldblum).  

Glinda, meanwhile, has become the glamorous symbol of Goodness for all of Oz, living at the palace in Emerald City and reveling in the perks of fame and popularity. Under the instruction of Madame Morrible (Oscar® winner Michelle Yeoh), Glinda is deployed to serve as an effervescent comfort to Oz, reassuring the masses that all is well under the rule of The Wizard.  

As Glinda’s stardom expands and she prepares to marry Prince Fiyero (Olivier award winner and Emmy and SAG nominee Jonathan Bailey) in a spectacular Ozian wedding, she is haunted by her separation from Elphaba. She attempts to broker a conciliation between Elphaba and The Wizard, but those efforts will fail, driving Elphaba and Glinda only further apart. The aftershocks will transform Boq (Tony nominee Ethan Slater) and Fiyero forever, and threaten the safety of Elphaba’s sister, Nessarose (Marissa Bode), when a girl from Kansas comes crashing into all their lives. 

As an angry mob rises against the Wicked Witch, Glinda and Elphaba will need to come together one final time. With their singular friendship now the fulcrum of their futures, they will need to truly see each other, with honesty and empathy, if they are to change themselves, and all of Oz, for good. 

Wicked: For Good also stars Emmy nominee Bowen Yang and Bronwyn James as Glinda’s fawning assistants, Pfannee and ShenShen and BAFTA and Grammy nominee Sharon D. Clarke (Caroline, or Change) as the voice of Elphaba’s childhood nanny, Dulcibear. 

The film is produced by returning Tony and Emmy winning powerhouse Marc Platt p.g.a. and by multiple Tony winner David Stone. The executive producers are Stephen Schwartz, David Nicksay, Jared LeBoff, Winnie Holzman and Dana Fox. The first film, Wicked, released in November 2024, earned 10 Academy Award® nominations, including Best Picture, and won the Oscars® for Costume Design and Production Design. To date, the film has grossed $750 million worldwide. 

Wicked: For Good is based on the generation-defining musical stage play with music and lyrics by legendary Grammy and Oscar® winning composer and lyricist Stephen Schwartz and book by Winnie Holzman, from the bestselling novel by Gregory Maguire. The screenplay is by Winnie Holzman and Winnie Holzman & Dana Fox. The film score is by John Powell & Stephen Schwartz, with music and lyrics by Stephen Schwartz.

snippet.title: VALORANT Champions Paris — Playoffs Stage — Day 15
snippet.description:
Welcome to the climax of the 2025 VALORANT Champions Tour! The biggest stage in VALORANT is ready, the lights of Paris are shining, and the countdown has begun. Following a season of historic rivalries, epic comebacks, and unforgettable moments, the world’s top teams now gather at Champions Paris.

From September 12 to October 5, the journey continues through Group Stage and Playoffs before the epic conclusion at the Grand Final with the crowning of the next World Champion. The Group Stage will feature 16 teams spread across four groups, with each group hosting one team from VALORANT's four International Leagues. In this stage, teams will battle through a double elimination format, advancing two teams out of each group. The 8 teams who make it out will be randomly seeded into a double elimination bracket, with teams from the same group placed on opposite sides of the bracket. Teams will compete through Best-of-3 matches until the final 2 matches which will be a Best-of-5. The last team standing will claim the title of VALORANT World Champion!

We’re proud to work with our fantastic partners throughout 2025: AWS, Coinbase, EWC, HyperX, Mastercard, OMEN, Red Bull, Secretlab, and Verizon.

snippet.description:
Written and Performed by: Mike kosa
Beat Produced by: Mike kosa
Recorded at 187 Mobstaz Studio
Mixed and Mastered by:  Gab Luciano
Directed and Edited by: Jc Echanes
Prod Manager by: Allen Cuento

Ian McShane

Alvin Prisno

*Lyrics*
Halika na't pasukin natin ang mundo ng laro
Mike Kosa, mas matindi pa sa mga Egoy at Kano
Kapag bumanat sa mic, katumbas ko’y ilang tumbok
Sa aking dila na hindi na nagbabago ng tunto
Hinasa ng panahon kasabay ng beatbox kong istilo
At inilapat ang mga letra, sintigas like Escudero
At ilang kwentong barbero ang aking natanggap
Ang masapawan ng pangalan ko, kay hirap matanggap
Ako ’yung bata na gustong gustong gawing bataan
Ng beterano, naturingang utak ay walang laman
Magco-compose ng English rap na ang puntirya’y magpa-bounce
Nagpapanggap na Englisero, mga bobong mag-pronounce
Full effect pero ang rhyming ay na-discorrect
Hindi ma-take ang pag-arte, sabi ni Direk
Wala kang karangalan para sa akin magyabang
Isa ka lang na tagahanga na gusto sa’kin mag-abang
Ikaw ay bata para sa’kin, ’wag kang magmagaling
Wala ka pa sa kalahati ng aking narrating
Ngayon ka pa lang sumisibol at biglang sumulpot
At kumpara sa’kin na kay dami ko nang nasundot
Na dahil lang sa pagrarap, kay dami nang nainggit
Pinapagana ko ay utak at hindi ang damit
Kasi ang iba ay nagrarap para lang sa chicas
Eh pano kung hindi na uso, bigla ka na lang lilikas?
Hindi usapan kung beterano o maging baguhan
O kung ang mic ay nasa kaliwa o nasa kanan
Ang importante para sa’kin ay maging malaya
Hindi ’yung tipong champion ka nang dahil lang sa daya
Hindi ka dapat mag-angas o umasta na sikat
Alam ko, alam mo rin na alam din ng lahat
Ika’y nagbibingi-bingihan at nagpapakadisente
Na sa tuwing ito ay topic, nagpapanggap kang inosente
Ang aking flow napakasimple pero ’di na uutal
Ang mga rhymes buong-buo pero malayong magbutal
Ipinamalas na ang husay sa mga klase ng duelo
Kung ikaw ang makakalaban, ’di ko kailangan pang bumuelo
Hindi naging basehan sa dami ng iyong alalay
Ang pagiging magaling wala sa estado ng buhay
Laki man sa Tondo walang sapat na pera
Aking kanta’y de-kalidad at yaman ko ang letra
Hindi ako nagbibitaw ng mga patapon
Isang talento na hindi pinansin ng ilang taon
Ako ’yung preso na pinapangarap mong bumaba
At gusto mo akong isama sa iyong pagkadapa
Ikaw ang nagsimula, ikaw ang unang nagpahangin
Binaba ko na ang lona mula sa pilakang tabing
’Di ka bagay mag-artista, tanggalin ang maskara
Batalyong aking nakalaban, tinumba ko mag-isa
Sa mga gustong maghari na ang trono ay buyon
Kung gusto mong maka-isa, humalik sa aking tumbong
With my group, Dos Talentos and 187 Mobsta
Sapul ang humahatol sa mahusay na makata - Mike Kosa!

Hinasa ng panahon kasabay ng beatbox kong istilo
At inilapat ang mga letra, sintigas like Escudero
At ilang kwentong barbero ang aking natanggap
Ang masapawan ng pangalan ko, kay hirap matanggap
Ako ’yung bata na gustong gustong gawing bataan
Ng beterano, naturingang utak ay walang laman
Magco-compose ng English rap na ang puntirya’y magpa-bounce
Nagpapanggap na Englisero, mga bobong mag-pronounce
Full effect pero ang rhyming ay na-discorrect
Hindi ma-take ang pag-arte, sabi ni Direk
Wala kang karangalan para sa akin magyabang
Isa ka lang na tagahanga na gusto sa’kin mag-abang
Ikaw ay bata para sa’kin, ’wag kang magmagaling
Wala ka pa sa kalahati ng aking narrating
Ngayon ka pa lang sumisibol at biglang sumulpot
At kumpara sa’kin na kay dami ko nang nasundot
Na dahil lang sa pagrarap, kay dami nang nainggit
Pinapagana ko ay utak at hindi ang damit
Kasi ang iba ay nagrarap para lang sa chicas
Eh pano kung hindi na uso, bigla ka na lang lilikas?
Hindi usapan kung beterano o maging baguhan
O kung ang mic ay nasa kaliwa o nasa kanan
Ang importante para sa’kin ay maging malaya
Hindi ’yung tipong champion ka nang dahil lang sa daya
Hindi ka dapat mag-angas o umasta na sikat
Alam ko, alam mo rin na alam din ng lahat
Ika’y nagbibingi-bingihan at nagpapakadisente
Na sa tuwing ito ay topic, nagpapanggap kang inosente
Ang aking flow napakasimple pero ’di na uutal
Ang mga rhymes buong-buo pero malayong magbutal
Ipinamalas na ang husay sa mga klase ng duelo
Kung ikaw ang makakalaban, ’di ko kailangan pang bumuelo
Hindi naging basehan sa dami ng iyong alalay
Ang pagiging magaling wala sa estado ng buhay
Laki man sa Tondo walang sapat na pera
Aking kanta’y de-kalidad at yaman ko ang letra
Hindi ako nagbibitaw ng mga patapon
Isang talento na hindi pinansin ng ilang taon
Ako ’yung preso na pinapangarap mong bumaba
At gusto mo akong isama sa iyong pagkadapa
Ikaw ang nagsimula, ikaw ang unang nagpahangin
Binaba ko na ang lona mula sa pilakang tabing
’Di ka bagay mag-artista, tanggalin ang maskara
Batalyong aking nakalaban, tinumba ko mag-isa
Sa mga gustong maghari na ang trono ay buyon
Kung gusto mong maka-isa, humalik sa aking tumbong
With my group, Dos Talentos and 187 Mobsta
Sapul ang humahatol sa mahusay na makata - Mike Kosa!

snippet.title: Minamahal - Ashtine Olviga and Andres Muhlach (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
#ashtineolviga #andresmuhlach  #minamahal #vivarecords
The Official Music Video of 'Minamahal' Rendition of Ashtine Olviga & Andres Muhlach

Ashtine Olviga and Andres Muhlach breathe new life into Dana Paulene and Earl Agustin’s heartfelt ballad “Minamahal.” Their rendition transforms the already tender love song into a duet that feels both cinematic and deeply personal, especially since it's going to be one of the soundtracks for their upcoming film. With Ashtine’s warm, emotive vocals intertwining seamlessly with Andres’ earnest delivery, the track highlights the delicate push-and-pull of affection, longing, and vulnerability. 

Composed by Earl Agustin, Amiel Isaac Sol
Published by Viva Music Publishing, Inc
Produced by Civ Fontanilla
Arranged by Tommy Katigbak

There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (“Robux”). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms.
